-- ADB, Kenya Sign $49 Million Agreement to Build Electricity Link to Uganda
-- Sarah McGregor
-- 2010-09-20T07:43:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-20/adb-kenya-sign-49-million-agreement-to-build-electricity-link-to-uganda.html

          
          
             Kenya and African Development Bank
signed a 3.97 billion-shilling agreement to build a power line
connecting to neighboring Uganda, Kenyan Finance Minister Uhuru
Kenyatta said.  
 The accord is part of a 16 billion-shilling program to
boost electricity supplies in five African nations including
Kenya, Democratic Republic of Congo, Rwanda, Uganda and Burundi,
Kenyatta told reporters in the capital, Nairobi, today.  
